ENTRY       EC 2.3.1.186                Enzyme
NAME        pseudotropine acyltransferase;
            pseudotropine:acyl-CoA transferase;
            tigloyl-CoA:pseudotropine acyltransferase;
            acetyl-CoA:pseudotropine acyltransferase;
            pseudotropine acetyltransferase;
            pseudotropine tigloyltransferase;
            PAT
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     acyl-CoA:pseudotropine O-acyltransferase
REACTION    an acyl-CoA + pseudotropine = CoA + an O-acylpseudotropine [RN:R08713]
ALL_REAC    R08713 > R06736
SUBSTRATE   acyl-CoA [CPD:C00040];
            pseudotropine [CPD:C02066]
PRODUCT     CoA [CPD:C00010];
            O-acylpseudotropine [CPD:C17378]
COMMENT     This enzyme exhibits absolute specificity for the exo/3beta configuration found in pseudotropine as tropine (tropan-3alpha-ol; see EC 2.3.1.185, tropine acyltransferase) and nortropine are not substrates [1]. Acts on a wide range of aliphatic acyl-CoA derivatives, including acetyl-CoA, beta-methylcrotonyl-CoA and tigloyl-CoA [1].
